01:25.720 --> 01:30.169
<i>My friends on the mainland think just because
I live in Hawaii, I live in paradise.</i>

01:30.960 --> 01:32.928
<i>Like a permanent vacation.</i>

01:32.920 --> 01:37.642
<i>We're all just out here sipping mai tais,
shaking our hips, and catching waves.</i>

01:38.360 --> 01:42.763
<i>Are they insane?
Do they think we 're immune to life?</i>

01:43.200 --> 01:46.679
<i>How can they possibly think our
families are less screwed up...</i>

01:46.680 --> 01:48.999
<i>...our cancers less fatal...</i>

01:49.000 --> 01:52.243
<i>...our heartaches less painful?</i>

01:52.240 --> 01:56.131
<i>Hell, I haven't been on</i> a
<i>surfboard in 15 years.</i>

01:59.040 --> 02:00.919
<i>For the last 23 days...</i>

02:00.920 --> 02:06.848
<i>...I've been living in a paradise of IVs
and urine bags and tracheal tubes.</i>

02:06.840 --> 02:08.568
<i>Paradise?</i>

02:09.320 --> 02:11.926
<i>Paradise can go fuck itself.</i>

02:19.560 --> 02:23.724
<i>This is Elizabeth
Thorson King, my wife.</i>

02:23.720 --> 02:25.006
<i>Twenty-three days ago...</i>

02:25.007 --> 02:28.639
<i>...she was launched from a powerboat
during a race and hit her head.</i>

02:28.640 --> 02:30.919
<i>Almost drowned.</i>

02:30.920 --> 02:36.609
<i>When I heard about the accident and
about the coma, I wasn't even in town.</i>

02:36.600 --> 02:41.925
<i>I was on Maui, on business, and
we hadn't spoken in three days.</i>

02:42.440 --> 02:45.603
<i>In a way, we hadn't
really spoken in months.</i>

02:49.400 --> 02:52.879
<i>If you're doing this to get my
attention, Liz, it's working.</i>

02:52.880 --> 02:54.839
<i>I'm ready now.</i>

02:54.840 --> 02:58.799
<i>I'm ready to talk.
I'm ready to change.</i>

02:58.800 --> 03:02.043
<i>I'm ready to be a real
husband and a real father.</i>

03:02.040 --> 03:04.202
<i>Just wake up.</i>

03:04.960 --> 03:07.281
<i>Please, Liz, just wake up.</i>

03:11.800 --> 03:13.131
Hey, Noe, what's up?

03:13.120 --> 03:15.485
<i>Matt, Scottie's teacher's
on the phone.</i>

03:15.486 --> 03:16.845
<i>She says it's urgent.</i>

03:16.846 --> 03:18.842
Okay, put her on.

03:21.400 --> 03:23.289
We don't think these
photographs...

03:23.290 --> 03:26.399
...are appropriate for Scottie to
be sharing with her classmates.

03:26.400 --> 03:30.279
Some of them went home quite disturbed,
and we got some angry calls from parents.

03:30.280 --> 03:33.919
Yeah, she's kind of been going to town
on this whole picture-taking thing.

03:33.920 --> 03:38.439
I had no idea.
Mr. King, we see this every day.

03:38.440 --> 03:42.399
Children acting out in school
when something is wrong at home.

03:42.400 --> 03:46.479
And your family is facing
a devastating crisis.

03:46.480 --> 03:50.166
Have you been engaging Scottie in talking
about everything that's going on?

03:50.160 --> 03:51.446
Yes, yes, absolutely.

03:51.447 --> 03:53.959
Encouraging her to
express her feelings?

03:53.960 --> 03:56.439
That's crucial. Mm-hm.
I understand.

03:56.440 --> 04:00.240
What's the matter with you, showing those
pictures of Mom for your art project?

04:00.240 --> 04:02.481
I'm a photographer, Dad,
a real photographer.

04:02.482 --> 04:04.801
No. You're overdoing it,
is what you're doing.

04:04.800 --> 04:06.006
I saw it in a book.

04:06.007 --> 04:10.159
Some famous photographer lady took
pictures of her mom in the hospital...

04:10.160 --> 04:12.845
...while she was dying, and
they're considered art.

04:12.840 --> 04:14.126
That's what I'm doing.

04:14.127 --> 04:17.119
First of all, your mother is
very sick, but she isn't dying.

04:17.120 --> 04:20.199
And second of all, we don't share
personal stuff with strangers.

04:20.200 --> 04:23.439
What's going on with
your mom is private.

04:23.440 --> 04:25.999
I'm hungry.
Can we get burgers? No.

04:26.000 --> 04:29.679
<i>The last time I took care of Scottie
by myself was when she was 3.</i>

04:29.680 --> 04:32.479
<i>Now she's 10, and I have no
idea what to do with her.</i>

04:32.480 --> 04:35.290
But I wanna eat now,
not in an hour.

04:35.280 --> 04:38.363
<i>And with Elizabeth in the
hospital, she's testing me.</i>

04:38.920 --> 04:42.519
<i>I'm the backup parent,
the understudy.</i>

04:42.520 --> 04:46.127
This is Matt King. I'm returning your call.
How can I help you?

04:46.120 --> 04:48.122
<i>It's your daughter Scottie.</i>

04:48.123 --> 04:52.079
<i>She's been texting some awful things to my
daughter, Lani, and I'd like her to stop.</i>

04:52.080 --> 04:54.719
<i>Huh.</i>

04:54.720 --> 04:57.479
<i>"We all know you grew
pubes over the summer."</i>

04:57.480 --> 05:01.405
<i>I mean, my daughter can't help it if she's
developing a little early for her age.</i>

05:01.400 --> 05:04.404
<i>You think that's nice?
Well, that's not like her at all.</i>

05:04.760 --> 05:06.999
She's usually very sweet.

05:07.000 --> 05:10.879
As you may know, her mother isn't well.
Maybe this is how she's dealing with it.

05:10.880 --> 05:13.879
<i>I'm very sorry about your
family situation, Mr. King...</i>

05:13.880 --> 05:16.719
<i>...but my daughter comes
home from school in tears.</i>

05:16.720 --> 05:19.007
Yeah, no, I get it I'm sorry.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.048
<i>Scottie's the one who
should be sorry.</i>

05:21.049 --> 05:23.079
<i>I want her to come
over and apologize...</i>

05:23.080 --> 05:26.119
<i>...and I don't ever want her
to text my daughter again.</i>

05:26.120 --> 05:29.567
<i>If she doesn't apologize, I'll
take it up with the dean.</i>

05:29.560 --> 05:32.245
<i>You can't buy your
way out of this.</i>

05:35.000 --> 05:36.889
Can you give me an address?

05:50.600 --> 05:52.364
Thank you for coming by.

05:53.640 --> 05:55.085
Hi.

05:56.840 --> 06:01.079
I forgot to mention Scottie said she didn't
wanna be Lani's partner at the rock wall...

06:01.080 --> 06:04.129
...because she didn't wanna fall
into my daughter's butt crack.

06:04.120 --> 06:07.169
That doesn't even make sense.
Ah.

06:08.760 --> 06:11.239
<i>Shirts off. Shirts off.</i>

06:11.240 --> 06:13.639
<i>Good, good, good, good job.</i>

06:13.640 --> 06:15.961
<i>I don't think she has any idea.</i>

06:15.960 --> 06:18.725
<i>That was very good, Bobby Brown.
Yeah. Here.</i>

06:19.120 --> 06:23.239
<i>Because she goes, "I'm living at this.
I'll meet you out in front." So...</i>

06:23.240 --> 06:26.961
Scottie, you have something
you wanna say to Lani?

06:26.960 --> 06:28.724
Sorry.

06:29.320 --> 06:31.607
<i>He knows he's going
away for a while.</i>

06:32.320 --> 06:36.159
<i>If he's got a chance, he's bolting. Great.
Well, it was nice meeting you both.</i>

06:36.160 --> 06:39.159
You should come over for a swim
or a hike or something, okay?

06:39.160 --> 06:41.162
I don't think she's
sorry at all.

06:41.160 --> 06:44.164
- She's gonna keep on doing it, I can tell.
- No, she won't.

06:44.560 --> 06:48.849
Look. Scottie, you're
gonna stop, right?

06:49.520 --> 06:52.126
And you're really,
really sorry, right?

06:53.280 --> 06:56.966
<i>Seems like every time I forget to pray,
we don't catch a guy for three days.</i>

06:56.960 --> 06:58.530
<i>I know, I'm telling you, man.</i>

07:02.000 --> 07:03.843
Oh, and, Mr. King? Yeah?

07:03.840 --> 07:05.080
Good luck with the sale.

07:06.240 --> 07:10.439
They say your decision will have a major
impact on Hawaii's real-estate world.

07:10.440 --> 07:12.761
Not to mention the whole
landscape of Kauai.

07:12.760 --> 07:15.001
Hundreds of millions
of dollars, yeah?

07:16.560 --> 07:18.239
Yeah. It's a big decision.

07:18.240 --> 07:22.519
My husband's family's from Kauai.
Hanapepe, born and bred.

07:22.520 --> 07:26.047
They hope you don't sell.
You don't say.

07:26.040 --> 07:28.646
All that traffic
it's gonna make.

07:33.200 --> 07:35.441
<i>As if Liz's coma weren't
enough already...</i>

07:35.442 --> 07:38.079
<i>...the whole goddamn state
is following my decision...</i>

07:38.080 --> 07:41.607
<i>...on who's gonna buy 25,000
pristine acres on Kauai...</i>

07:41.600 --> 07:44.490
<i>...that my family has
owned since the 1860s.</i>

07:45.040 --> 07:49.443
<i>A lot of my cousins are broke, and the
sale will make us all very, very rich.</i>

07:51.480 --> 07:54.479
<i>My family meets in six
days to approve a buyer.</i>

07:54.480 --> 07:57.723
<i>But ever since my father died,
I'm the sole trustee...</i>

07:57.720 --> 08:01.088
<i>...which means I alone
hold all the cards.</i>

08:05.800 --> 08:09.359
<i>My great-great-grandmother was
Princess Margaret Ke'alohilani...</i>

08:09.360 --> 08:12.364
<i>...one of the last direct
descendants of King Kamehameha.</i>

08:12.360 --> 08:14.806
<i>She was originally supposed
to marry her cousin...</i>

08:14.807 --> 08:17.759
<i>...but she fell in love with
Edward King, her haole banker...</i>

08:17.760 --> 08:20.039
<i>...whose parents had
been missionaries.</i>

08:20.040 --> 08:23.079
<i>Between his land deals and
her huge inheritance...</i>

08:23.080 --> 08:26.402
<i>...generations of their
descendants, all of us...</i>

08:26.400 --> 08:31.691
<i>...have watched the past unfurl millions
into our laps through leases and sales.</i>

08:33.320 --> 08:36.438
<i>Now something called the rule
against perpetuities...</i>

08:36.440 --> 08:38.760
<i>...is forcing us to
dissolve the trust...</i>

08:38.760 --> 08:43.368
<i>...and we're selling our last huge
parcel of virgin Hawaiian land.</i>

08:46.280 --> 08:49.727
<i>Unlike a lot of my cousins, I haven't
blown my share of the trust money.</i>

08:49.720 --> 08:51.449
<i>Just like my father before me...</i>

08:51.450 --> 08:54.359
<i>...I live only on the income
from my law practice.</i>

08:54.360 --> 08:57.839
<i>I don't want my daughters growing
up spoiled and entitled.</i>

08:57.840 --> 09:01.439
<i>Liz always accuses me of stinginess,
but I agree with my father.</i>

09:01.440 --> 09:05.479
<i>You give your children enough money to do
something, but not enough to do nothing.</i>

09:05.480 --> 09:07.209
Matt.

09:07.200 --> 09:09.009
Your cousins are here.

09:14.400 --> 09:18.359
<i>Not only am I the sole trustee, but I
specialize in real-estate transaction law...</i>

09:18.360 --> 09:22.410
<i>...so a few of the more involved cousins
have been meeting with me to analyze bids.</i>

09:22.400 --> 09:23.606
Hey. How's it, Matt?

09:23.607 --> 09:27.399
<i>Cousin Hal, Cousin
Milo, Cousin Stan...</i>

09:27.400 --> 09:30.559
<i>...Cousin Six, Cousin
Wink, Cousin Connie...</i>

09:30.560 --> 09:32.279
How you doing? Okay?

09:32.280 --> 09:35.119
<i>...and Cousin Dave, both of
whom oppose the sale entirely.</i>

09:35.120 --> 09:37.999
<i>- Good to see you.
- Don't be fooled by appearances.</i>

09:38.000 --> 09:41.719
<i>In Hawaii, some of the most powerful
people look like bums and stuntmen.</i>

09:41.720 --> 09:43.484
All right, so where are we?

09:43.480 --> 09:45.289
<i>Proposals are
virtually the same.</i>

09:45.290 --> 09:48.279
<i>Hotels, shopping centers,
condos and golf courses.</i>

09:48.280 --> 09:49.839
I have some major concerns...

09:49.840 --> 09:52.679
<i>A Chicago group is offering
half a billion dollars.</i>

09:52.680 --> 09:56.319
<i>But we're leaning towards a lower
bid from a guy named Don Holitzer.</i>

09:56.320 --> 10:00.039
<i>He's actually from Kauai.
Made a fortune in Silicon Valley.</i>

10:00.040 --> 10:03.679
<i>Old Cousin Hugh is pushing us in
that direction, and I say, why not?</i>

10:03.680 --> 10:06.519
<i>The money would come from
Hawaii and stay in Hawaii.</i>

10:06.520 --> 10:10.286
There's nothing about saving the heiau.
You know, it's ridiculous.

10:10.280 --> 10:14.285
And there's no beach access like they
say, and that's really, really...

10:20.480 --> 10:23.768
<i>Elizabeth's gonna make it out okay.
I know it.</i>

10:23.760 --> 10:25.808
<i>It's not her time yet.</i>

10:29.280 --> 10:30.679
<i>She'll wake up.</i>

10:30.680 --> 10:33.519
<i>Scottie and Alexandra will
have their mother back.</i>

10:33.520 --> 10:35.648
<i>And we'll talk about
our marriage.</i>

10:35.640 --> 10:38.246
<i>I know I can make things right.</i>

10:38.880 --> 10:43.319
<i>I'll sell the land, quit my practice,
and buy her whatever she wants.</i>

10:43.320 --> 10:46.479
<i>A big boat. A house in France.</i>

10:46.480 --> 10:49.563
<i>We'll take a trip around the
world, just the two of us.</i>

10:49.560 --> 10:53.167
<i>We'll get close again,
like the early days.</i>

10:54.200 --> 10:57.249
<i>I wish I had better
news, Matthew.</i>

10:57.240 --> 11:01.768
<i>But Dr. Chun and Dr. Mueller and
I agree that her condition...</i>

11:02.240 --> 11:04.599
...it's deteriorating.

11:04.600 --> 11:07.759
She has no eye movement, she
has no pupillary responses...

11:07.760 --> 11:13.519
...she has no brain-stem
reflexes whatsoever.

11:13.520 --> 11:19.926
I mean, the machines can keep her alive, but
the quality of her life would be so poor.

11:19.920 --> 11:22.844
Basically the way it is now.

11:24.600 --> 11:28.082
She'll never be the
way she was, Matt.

11:28.080 --> 11:29.605
Never.

11:30.000 --> 11:31.968
We know that now.

11:36.200 --> 11:37.850
Look, uh ""

11:39.000 --> 11:42.959
I can't tell you how sorry
I am to tell you this.

11:42.960 --> 11:45.964
And you do have your daughters.

11:45.960 --> 11:49.123
There's just nothing
more that we can do.

11:55.240 --> 11:57.879
So if we do go ahead and
take her off the machines...

11:57.880 --> 11:59.644
There's no "if."

11:59.640 --> 12:03.964
It's "when." I have a legal obligation.
You know that.

12:08.760 --> 12:10.919
How long will she last?

12:10.920 --> 12:12.479
Well, it's hard to say.

12:12.480 --> 12:15.639
It could be a few days, it
could be a couple of weeks.

12:15.640 --> 12:20.931
For planning purposes, I think you should
work off the shortest possible scenario.

12:20.920 --> 12:25.289
I know I've gotta get the ball rolling
on the organ donations right away.

12:27.360 --> 12:28.885
Matt.

12:30.200 --> 12:33.170
Elizabeth has many friends.

12:33.160 --> 12:35.288
She has a big life.

12:37.280 --> 12:39.851
If you're gonna let everybody
know to say goodbye...

12:39.840 --> 12:44.528
...which is the typical protocol for
these situations, you start now.

12:45.880 --> 12:48.406
Then when the last day comes...

12:49.120 --> 12:51.600
...they'll feel more ready.

12:52.680 --> 12:56.287
Or as ready as they can feel
for something like this.

12:59.200 --> 13:01.680
I'm so sorry, Matt.

13:44.960 --> 13:47.008
Hey. Hey. There he is.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.764
How's it going? What's going on?

13:48.765 --> 13:51.519
She was looking a little pale
lately, all cooped up here.

13:51.520 --> 13:55.411
I know she'd be mortified if nobody helped
her out with some lipstick and blush.

13:55.400 --> 13:56.686
I know she'll grill me.

13:56.687 --> 13:59.604
Of course, Kai's getting her
caught up on the latest gossip.

13:59.600 --> 14:02.604
Well, I don't wanna start
from scratch later.

14:03.040 --> 14:04.769
Oh, and, Matt, uh,
on the way here...

14:04.770 --> 14:08.128
...we stopped by and put some meals
in your fridge, all ready to nuke.

14:08.120 --> 14:09.360
Mm-hm.

14:10.520 --> 14:12.761
So, what's the latest, anyway, Matt?
Any updates?

14:13.920 --> 14:15.160
Just more of the same.

14:15.161 --> 14:18.004
Just keeping the kidneys and
other vital organs working...

14:18.000 --> 14:20.606
...and hoping for the best.

15:10.080 --> 15:12.765
The food at the club is so good.

15:12.760 --> 15:14.524
Yeah, they do a good job here.
Come here.

15:14.525 --> 15:15.806
Mm.

15:17.320 --> 15:21.325
Why is it called a jellyfish?
It's not a fish, it's not jelly.

15:21.320 --> 15:22.651
I have no idea.

15:23.080 --> 15:26.448
You ask good questions, Scottie.
You're getting too smart for me.

15:26.920 --> 15:29.491
I'm gonna ask Mom
when she wakes up.

15:29.920 --> 15:33.083
Do you think she's gonna
know everything she used to?

15:33.080 --> 15:34.730
I don't know.

15:48.080 --> 15:49.889
I'll be right back.

15:51.240 --> 15:54.801
- Hi, Matt. Hi, Scottie.
- Troy.

15:54.800 --> 15:58.327
So, what's going on?
I mean, how's Elizabeth doing?

15:58.840 --> 16:00.205
The same.

16:00.200 --> 16:03.090
Well, you know, I went and
visited her last week...

16:03.880 --> 16:05.564
...and, uh, she
looked pretty good.

16:05.565 --> 16:07.559
Then why'd you ask?
I don't know.

16:07.560 --> 16:10.399
I guess I just wanted to
know what the latest is.

16:10.400 --> 16:15.359
You know, I've been praying for her every
day, you guys, really hard, seriously.

16:15.360 --> 16:18.759
And, well, what I meant to say was
when I was there, I talked to her...

16:18.760 --> 16:21.359
...and she moved her hand.

16:21.360 --> 16:23.399
And then I was, like...
I was encouraged.

16:23.400 --> 16:25.562
I thought that that was
an encouraging sign.

16:25.560 --> 16:27.085
That's enough.

16:28.400 --> 16:31.768
I really think she heard me.
Look, Troy, go to your friends.

16:31.760 --> 16:34.843
There's no hard feelings.
Let's just leave it alone.

16:41.080 --> 16:42.719
I told you, Matt.

16:42.720 --> 16:46.039
The water that day was so choppy.
I've told you a hundred times.

16:46.040 --> 16:48.239
What happened to her
could've happened to me.

16:48.240 --> 16:50.679
The ocean was brutal that day.
Ask anybody.

16:50.680 --> 16:53.919
You weren't supposed to be driving.
She was supposed to be driving.

16:53.920 --> 16:55.479
She wanted me to drive.

16:55.480 --> 16:58.759
She's the one that told me to pass
the other boat before the turn.

16:58.760 --> 17:01.279
You know, it's just your
whole attitude towards me.

17:01.280 --> 17:04.807
I didn't...
You know, I feel terrible about it.

17:04.800 --> 17:07.929
Plus, I almost drowned
myself when the boat caps...

17:10.280 --> 17:11.964
Hey.

17:13.319 --> 17:16.959
Scottie! Hey, Scottie! Scottie!

17:16.960 --> 17:19.849
Hey. Listen.

17:19.839 --> 17:21.683
Don't pay any attention
to that guy.

17:21.684 --> 17:23.762
That guy's a dope. I hate him.

17:23.760 --> 17:25.922
Yeah, I know.

17:26.640 --> 17:29.039
Hey, let's do something crazy.

17:29.040 --> 17:32.119
Let's drive to the airport, we'll
hop over to the Big Island...

17:32.120 --> 17:34.639
...and we'll surprise your sister.
What do you say?

17:34.640 --> 17:37.799
Right now? Yeah, it'll be fun.
She's not expecting us.

17:37.800 --> 17:39.959
And we can bring her home.

17:39.960 --> 17:43.931
I think she should be with us, don't you?
Don't you miss her? I miss her.

17:43.920 --> 17:46.890
Yeah. I mean, I'm out of school.
She should be too.

17:47.520 --> 17:50.205
There you go. Okay.

17:50.200 --> 17:52.123
Let's go. Come on.

17:56.840 --> 17:58.842
Hey, Troy.

18:08.920 --> 18:13.079
<i>Somehow it feels natural to find a
daughter of mine on a different island.</i>

18:13.080 --> 18:15.919
<i>- A family seems exactly</i>-

18:15.920 --> 18:19.561
<i>All part of the same whole but
still separate and alone...</i>

18:19.560 --> 18:22.530
<i>...and always drifting
slowly apart.</i>

18:59.560 --> 19:01.608
That's the wrong door.

19:05.520 --> 19:08.364
Go back to sleep, Braelynn.
It's okay.

19:18.840 --> 19:20.559
Wake up your roommate, please.

19:20.560 --> 19:25.248
Um, Alex isn't here.
Where is she?

19:25.240 --> 19:29.723
I think she's somewhere outside.
Where outside?

19:30.920 --> 19:32.206
Hit it that way.

19:32.207 --> 19:35.727
No, between there. Fuckhead.

19:35.720 --> 19:37.447
Why are you hitting it that way?

19:37.448 --> 19:39.681
You're supposed to be
going through... Dude.

19:39.682 --> 19:42.331
Hey, girls!
What do you think you're doing?

19:42.320 --> 19:44.209
